name: San Android Cento
description:
Fifth track of the dream_logs visual album by ethereal_interface minted to HEN
This is the first time this album will exist in the digital sphere as it was originally released via Circuit Church on VHS tape only. 

Tracks are partially trimmed due to mb limit so the full experience still only exists somewhere out there on VHS!

Video by Sky Goodman
Music by modal_plane (ex_mortal)
Dance by Cristal Sabbagh

Lyrics:

Sad Android Cento

We will, we will know
Freedom at last
Like the ones who
Travelled distance oceans
Conditioned, behind my eye
(Behind my eye)
Unstable conditions
Something I can only
Dream that, you will, you will know

In the wake of ash covered landscapes
Broken briefcases, smart car, market crash
I saw Boomers and Millennials in a monotonous glow

Fiction will drag this dream into a random sample

Hold the only one you need
Hold the only one you need

The whole thing, it's all been one big
short circuit.
